---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Disclosure - Michael Vivirito"
  description="Affiliate and sponsorship disclosure for michaelvivirito.com."
  keywords="disclosure, affiliate, FTC, sponsorship, Amazon Associates"
  ogTitle="Disclosure - Michael Vivirito"
  ogDescription="How affiliate links and sponsorships work on this site."
  canonical="/disclosure"
>
  <section>
    <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <h1>Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">How affiliate links and sponsorships work on this site.</p>
      <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">Last updated: June 7, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="card" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">

      <h2>Plain Language</h2>
      <p>
        Some links on this site, particularly on the
        <a href="/recommends">recommendations</a> page and inside certain
        articles, are <strong>affiliate links</strong>. If you click one and buy
        something, I may earn a small commission. The price you pay is the same
        either way.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Link To</h2>
      <p>
        I only link to gear and software I actually use, own, or have used at
        length. If I stop using it, the link comes down. I won't link to
        something just because the program pays well.
      </p>

      <h2>Programs I Participate In</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Amazon Associates</strong> &mdash; as an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases.</li>
        <li>Other programs may be added over time; they'll all be listed here.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Affiliate Links Are Marked</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate links carry <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in the HTML and open
        in a new tab. Pages that contain any affiliate link also display a
        plain-language note at the top so you know before you click.
      </p>

      <h2>Where the Money Goes</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate income helps fund <a href="/openworld">OpenWorld</a> and the
        cost of running the <a href="/homelab">homelab</a>. It does not change
        what I recommend, what I write about, or what makes it onto the site.
      </p>

      <h2>Sponsorships and Reviews</h2>
      <p>
        I currently take no paid placements, no paid reviews, and no sponsored
        posts. If that changes, this page will say so plainly before any
        sponsored content goes live.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a> if anything here is unclear.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto 0; text-align: center;">
      <p>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary">← Home</a>
        <a href="/recommends" class="btn btn-secondary">Recommendations</a>
        <a href="/openworld" class="btn btn-primary">OpenWorld</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
